            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/call-of-duty-black-ops-7">Call of Duty: Black Ops 7</a> is out today, and as such swarms of people are trying out the new campaign to see the latest development in the beloved Black Ops narrative. To their surprise, they're discovering a few quirks proving to be a tad frustrating.</p>
<p>Many of these problems stem from the solo experience. For one, the Call of Duty campaign cannot be paused, even if you're playing on your own. The narrative focuses on a squad of characters, but no AI companions come in to replace the role another player would.</p>
<p>It has no checkpoint system, meaning if you quit out of the game for any reason you'll have to start a mission over from the beginning. Also, the campaign requires an online connection at all times, meaning if you suddenly go offline for whatever reason (including game updates which can appear daily and without warning) you'll lose progress.</p>

